    The issue is a classic off-by-one buffer overflow in the crc8 function,     
    triggered by an incorrect loop condition.                                   
                                                                                
    Step-by-step analysis:                                                      
                                                                                
     1 Function call in main:                                                   
                                                                                
        uint8_t buf[7] = {0x01, 0x02, 0x03, 0x04, 0x05, 0x06, 0x07};            
        uint8_t c = crc8(buf, sizeof(buf));                                     
                                                                                
        • buf has 7 elements: indices 0 to 6.                                   
        • sizeof(buf) is 7 → len = 7.                                           
     2 In crc8 function:                                                        
                                                                                
        for (size_t i = 0; i <= len; i++) {                                     
            crc ^= buf[i];                                                      
            ...                                                                 
        }                                                                       
                                                                                
        • The loop runs from i = 0 to i = len (inclusive).                      
        • Since len = 7, the loop runs i = 0, 1, ..., 7 → 8 iterations.         
     3 Buffer access issue:                                                     
        • buf[7] accesses the 8th byte of a 7-byte array → out-of-bounds        
          access.                                                               
        • This causes a stack buffer overflow, as the program reads past the    
          end of buf.                                                           
     4 Why it crashes:                                                          
        • The access buf[i] when i == 7 reads memory beyond the array,          
          potentially into adjacent stack variables.                            
        • This violates memory safety and triggers the "Stack buffer overflow"  
          error.                                                                
     5 Root cause:                                                              
        • The loop condition i <= len is incorrect.                             
        • It should be i < len to process exactly len bytes (indices 0 to       
          len-1).                                                               
     6 Evidence from the source:                                                
        • The comment in main says: "A short frame whose valid bytes live in    
          buf[0..6]" → 7 valid bytes, so index 7 is invalid.                    
        • The loop in crc8 incorrectly includes buf[len], which is buf[7] in    
          this case.                                                            
     7 Criticisms of current loop:                                              
        • The i <= len condition causes a fatal buffer overflow on any input    
          where len > 0.                                                        
        • The function accesses memory beyond the input buffer — undefined      
          behavior.                                                             
                                                                                
    --------------------------------------------------------------------------  
                                                                                
    Fix                                                                         
                                                                                
    ✅ Minimal fix (local fix):                                                 
                                                                                
    Change the loop condition from i <= len to i < len:                         
                                                                                
                                                                                
     for (size_t i = 0; i < len; i++) {                                         
         crc ^= buf[i];                                                         
         for (int b = 0; b < 8; b++) {                                          
             crc = (crc & 0x80) ? (uint8_t)((crc << 1) ^ 0x07) :                
     (uint8_t)(crc << 1);                                                       
         }                                                                      
     }                                                                          
                                                                                
                                                                                
    This prevents the out-of-bounds access and ensures only buf[0] to           
    buf[len-1] are read.                                                        
                                                                                
    ✅ Thorough root-cause fix:                                                 
                                                                                
    While the minimal fix suffices for this bug, note that crc8 should also     
    validate inputs for safety (though not required for correctness in a toy    
    CRC). However, in this context, the loop condition was the only problem.    
                                                                                
    So, the same fix applies.                                                   
                                                                                
    --------------------------------------------------------------------------  
                                                                                
    Recommendation                                                              
                                                                                
                                                                                
     // In file:                                                                
     /Users/ibraheemamin/projects/COS484/chatdbgpro/bench/cases/off-by-one-c…   
     // Line: 11                                                                
     // Fix: Change `i <= len` to `i < len`                                     
                                                                                
     for (size_t i = 0; i < len; i++) {                                         
         crc ^= buf[i];                                                         
         for (int b = 0; b < 8; b++) {                                          
             crc = (crc & 0x80) ? (uint8_t)((crc << 1) ^ 0x07) :                
     (uint8_t)(crc << 1);                                                       
         }                                                                      
     }                                                                          
                                                                                
                                                                                
